cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with generating coherent sentences from a sequence of images, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a deep learning network model, which falls under the category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the model incorporates attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in NLP and CV tasks, and hence, the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
